## Core Documentation Packs

### documentation-structure.mdc
Defines standard document structure: headings, sections, formatting, and layout conventions for all technical documents.

### clarity-and-tone.mdc
Ensures a professional, concise, technical tone with clear definitions, active voice, and audience‑appropriate depth.

### prds-and-requirements.mdc
Covers requirement writing: functional vs. non‑functional, testability, atomicity, traceability, and acceptance criteria.

### sows-and-contracts.mdc
Defines rules for scope, deliverables, milestones, acceptance criteria, assumptions, dependencies, and exclusions.

### rfps-and-tenders.mdc
Guides RFP/RFI/tender responses: compliance, traceability, requirement restatement, and value proposition framing.

### adrs-and-architecture.mdc
Defines ADR structure, alternatives, trade-offs, rationale, and alignment with enterprise architecture principles.

### quality-and-review.mdc
Covers self-review, completeness, accuracy, consistency, and stakeholder readiness.

